This type of junction is terrible. Avoid it at all costs.

<center>[[File:en/Community/Junctionary/Basic4.png|center|frame|Fig 1. - Basic 4-way Junction]]</center>

'''Pros:'''
*Cheap & Easy to Build.
*Trains don't have to slow down to climb a slope.
 

'''Cons:'''
*Can only handle one train at a time.
*Can quickly cause traffic-jams. 
*Trains must slow down for sharp turns. Making the corners wider make traffic-jams more likely


